<p><font size="3" face="Arial">ChromoViz is an R package for multimodal visualization of microarray data,&nbsp;<br>  
DNA copy number alterations,           
 cross-platform and cross-species comparisons,&nbsp;<br>  
 and genomic non-expression data&nbsp;obtained from public databases onto chromosomes.<br>            
</font>
<table border="1" width="817" cellpadding="3" cellspacing="0">
  <tr>
    <td width="462" rowspan="2"> 
      <p align="center"><b><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><a href=http://bioinformatics.oupjournals.org/cgi/content/abstract/bth052?ijkey=51VafyFuBmjUE&keytype=ref>ChromoViz: Multimodal  
      visualization of gene expression profile onto chromosomes using Scalable   
        Vector Graphics.&nbsp;<a href="GOChaseAdvAcc.pdf"><font face="Times New Roman" size="2"><br>
      </font></a>
      </a><br>
        </font> </b><font face="Times New Roman" size="2"><i>Jihoon Kim, Hee-Joon   
        Chung, Chan Hee Park, Woong Yang Park, Ju Han Kim&nbsp; <b><br> 
      </b></i></font><b><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><font face="Times New Roman" size="2"><a href="ChromoViz_Bioinformatics04.pdf"><img border="0" src="../../pdf.gif" width="38" height="41" align="middle"></a></font></font><font face="Times New Roman" size="2"> 
      </font></b><a href="ChromoViz_Bioinformatics04.pdf"><font face="Times New Roman" size="2"><i><b>Bioinformatics 2004;20:1191-1192</b></i></font><b><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">&nbsp; 
